St Mirren 's Steven Thompson has apologised to team-mate John McGinn with a pole in training .
The Scotland Under 21 player is now on crutches and will miss the rest of the season after a prank at Saints ' Renfrewshire ground went wrong on Thursday .
Gary Teale 's first-team squad were doing a dribbling drill when veteran Thompson lost possession to McGinn .
Thompson scored two goals in Saints 4-1 win over Kilmarnock on Saturday .